Here's a PlantUML sequence diagram representing the control flow of the jlhood_retweet-leaderboard system:

```plantuml
@startuml jlhood_retweet-leaderboard

participant "Twitter Event Source" as TES
participant "TweetProcessorHandler" as TPH
participant "TweetProcessor" as TP
participant "Tweet" as T
participant "Leaderboard" as LB
participant "DynamoDB" as DDB
participant "API Gateway" as APIG
participant "GetLeaderboardHandler" as GLH
participant "Client" as C

TES -> TPH: Invoke with tweet JSON
activate TPH

TPH -> TP: processTweet(tweetJson)
activate TP

TP -> T: parse(tweetJson)
activate T
T --> TP: Tweet object
deactivate T

TP -> TP: filterTweet(tweet)
TP -> TP: convertToRetweetCount(tweet)

TP -> LB: updateLeaderboard(retweetCount)
activate LB

LB -> DDB: getItem(username)
activate DDB
DDB --> LB: LeaderboardRecord
deactivate DDB

LB -> LB: updateRecord(record, retweetCount)

LB -> DDB: putItem(updatedRecord)
activate DDB
DDB --> LB: Confirmation
deactivate DDB

LB --> TP: Update confirmation
deactivate LB

TP --> TPH: Processing complete
deactivate TP

TPH --> TES: Lambda execution complete
deactivate TPH

C -> APIG: GET /leaderboard
activate APIG

APIG -> GLH: Invoke
activate GLH

GLH -> LB: getLeaderboard(limit)
activate LB

LB -> DDB: scan()
activate DDB
DDB --> LB: All LeaderboardRecords
deactivate DDB

LB -> LB: sortAndLimitRecords()
LB --> GLH: Sorted leaderboard
deactivate LB

GLH --> APIG: JSON response
deactivate GLH

APIG --> C: Leaderboard data
deactivate APIG

@enduml
```